{
  "text": "\u2113 + 1]. -When f = f k-CS , [CITATION_1] shows a choice of R 1 such that |R 2 | \u2264 k 3 \u2212 k. We need (k 3 \u2212 k)(2k 2 \u2212 3k + 2) \u2113\u22121 \u2264 n\u2212 k, namely n \u2265 k[(k 2 \u2212 1)(2k 2 \u2212 3k + 2) \u2113\u22121 + 1].",
